{"build_type":"library","description":"MCP assessor (SM.1): creates the AF_INET listen socket (bind+listen), then runs a FOREVER accept loop (accept-connection-feeding-work-item-forever) pushing one {conn} work-item per connection into the collector; never returns, never closes the stream. Per-connection handler workers do the request I/O and reply. [hardened per Fable: bind() result checked (fault->supervisor restarts=retry), getsockname verifies the socket is actually on 8765 (structurally prevents silently listening on an auto-assigned ephemeral port), listen() result checked; any anomaly aborts loudly instead of falling through.]","module_name":"produce-protocol-connection-worklist-feeding-collector","package_name":"produce-protocol-connection-worklist-feeding-collector","function_definitions":{"produce-protocol-connection-worklist-feeding-collector":{"return_type":"i64","parameter_definitions":[{"parameter_name":"channel","parameter_type":"i64"}],"execution_instructions":[{"instruction_type":"variable_declaration","variable_name":"three","variable_type":"i64","assignment_operation":"literal","source_target":3},{"instruction_type":"variable_declaration","variable_name":"c8","variable_type":"i64","assignment_operation":"literal","source_target":8},{"instruction_type":"variable_declaration","variable_name":"d_bind","variable_type":"str","assignment_operation":"string","source_target":"mcp-assessor: bind(8765) failed; refusing to serve on a wrong port\n"},{"instruction_type":"variable_declaration","variable_name":"d_port","variable_type":"str","assignment_operation":"string","source_target":"mcp-assessor: socket bound to the WRONG port (not 8765); aborting\n"},{"instruction_type":"variable_declaration","variable_name":"d_listen","variable_type":"str","assignment_operation":"string","source_target":"mcp-assessor: listen() failed; aborting\n"},{"instruction_type":"variable_declaration","variable_name":"zero","variable_type":"i64","assignment_operation":"literal","sou